Color
. Non-metallic (Fig. 14) Head (Fig. 15) completely black, the eye darkly reddish, the mesosoma yelloworange overall, including the mesoscutum, scutellum, axillae and mesopleuron, except for the pronotum, which is completely black (
Fig. 17
), and part of the propodeum, which is brown; the gaster is brownish (
Fig. 17
). Antenna (Fig. 15): radicle black, scape broad foliaceous with base and apical area white, rest black; pedicel completely black except apex orange-white; F1 to F4 black, F5 basal 2/3 (
90 µm
) black and apically white (
50 µm
), F6 and clava completely white. Legs, including coxae, entirely white-yellow except for dark tarsus.
